description: These chicken dumplings can be eaten simply steamed or sealed in a pan for a little crispiness.
name: Chicken & Cabbage Dumplings Recipe | Woolworths
recipeIngredient: 1 tsp sesame oil (plus extra for frying)

recipeInstructions.text: Place the water chestnuts, spring onions, ginger, garlic and cabbage in a food processor and pulse to a coarse mix. Tip into a large bowl, add the chicken, soy sauce, sesame oil and oyster sauce and mix well.
Spoon a teaspoon of filling along one half of each wonton wrapper. Spread out slightly and fold the other half over, pleating the edges with a little bit of water to stick.

Steam the dumplings for 10-12 minutes until the chicken is cooked and the wrappers are translucent. Heat a drizzle of oil in a large non-stick pan and fry each dumpling for 1-2 minutes on each side, if desired.
